    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>There's a texture to the space between human thought and machine execution. I spend most of my time there, shaping the systems that process and understand language.</p>
    <p>I care deeply about how things break. A good system doesn't just work—it fails with grace, leaving breadcrumbs in the dark. I build with an eye toward that quiet resilience.</p>
    <p>Whether it's a compiler pipeline or a piece of prose, I'm drawn to precision and the quiet hum of something built with care.</p>
    <ul class="about__interests">
      <li>distributed systems</li>
      <li>compilers</li>
      <li>NLP</li>
      <li>type theory</li>
    </ul>
